-- ICICI Bank Plans to Raise $150 Million Selling 10-Year Subordinated Notes
-- B y   S h e l l e y   S m i t h
-- 2010-11-16T04:16:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-16/icici-bank-plans-to-raise-150-million-selling-10-year-subordinated-notes.html
ICICI Bank Ltd. plans to sell $150
million of 10-year subordinated notes as soon as today,
according to a person familiar with the matter.  The bank is offering the lower Tier 2 notes to investors to
yield in the low 7 percent area, said the person, who asked not
to be identified because the details are private. ICICI Bank
U.K. Plc is selling the debt, the person said.  Barclays Plc, Deutsche Bank AG and HSBC Holdings Plc are
managing the sale, the person said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shelley Smith in Hong Kong at 
 ssmith118@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Hugh Chow at 
 hchow12@bloomberg.net  